  "commentary": "With SPX at 6763.31 sitting just below the major negative gamma wall at 6765 (-6893M), dealers are likely buying the dip aggressively as their short gamma positioning forces them to chase price lower. The PIN regime confirms dealers are long gamma overall and will provide stabilizing flows, but the immediate proximity to max negative gamma at 6765 creates amplified buying pressure that should support a bounce toward the 6800 positive gamma wall (+6480M). Key levels are the 6765 negative gamma floor below (strong support) and 6800 ceiling above where dealers will sell rallies hard.\n\nBottom line: expect a bounce off current levels with upside capped near 6800.",
